  "text": "One of the important issues of the planar view on the molecular interaction map is that the abstraction does not provide clear boundaries for delineating the planes and many molecules can be arguably captured in multiple planes. For instance, Cdc6 is a structural component of the pre-replicative complex, which also inhibits the activity of B-type cyclins by its direct binding [CITATION_1] . Moreover, the physiological feedbacks provided from the structural plane to the signaling and checkpoint planes (e.g. morphological changes) are difficult to capture in the current graphical notation schema. However, the tri-planar view of the cell-cycle interactions captures the important regulatory controls implicated in the progression of the yeast cell cycle and provides a framework to identify control motifs, which we study next.",
